INSERT INTO Books VALUES(47,'Songs of Insurrection','Jc Kang',NULL,'Fiction','Fiction',NULL,'2021-01-05','','English','New TBR','197006708X','SPFBO 2018 Semi-Finalist. Lose yourself in this fusion of Asian and Western fantasy, which critics extol as "wonderfully opulent," "Breathtaking," and "Unique." Only the lost magic of Dragon Songs can save the world. Only an awkward girl with the perfect voice can rediscover it. The Dragon Singers of old summoned typhoons and routed armies, liberating mankind from the orcs before fading into legend. Now, with the world again facing a new cataclysm, the power of music stirs in Kaiya, an a na├»ve misfit with the perfect voice. Without a master to guide her, she must rely on Hardeep, a disgraced foreign paladin, to help awaken her latent magic. His motives might not be entirely noble. When he leads her to the fabled Dragon Scale Lute, which only a Dragon Singer can wield, it is up to Black Lotus Clan to intervene. Because the instrument''s fell power can save the world... Or destroy it.',1,'1752824334067.0','1752824334067.0','http://books.google.com/books/content?id=m6WBzgEACAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api',NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO Books VALUES(48,'The Talon Princess','J C Rose','J.C. Rose','Fiction','Fiction','J.C. Rose','2024-01-27','','English','New TBR','9798218354961','She saved her sister, but can she save herself? In a world where dreams of knighthood meet the cold reality of destruction, Isabel, a skilled archer, witnesses her home razed by a mysterious hooded warrior. A forbidden name escapes his lips, one that Isabel''s mother warns her never to repeat. Forced into a desperate flight with her sister, clutching a broken relic and a locked chest, they seek refuge in the abandoned city of Accreton. Within its mythical tapestries, a foreboding curse casts its ominous shadow, revealing long-forgotten families and a dangerous narrative that Isabel wishes she had never uncovered. Guided by road tales and haunted by memories of a perilous forest, Isabel discovers that some stories are better left forgotten. At times, it seems silence and knowledge, or the lack of it, are her only allies. Perhaps it might be best to know little and ask less. But Isabel quickly learns ignorance is the death of the innocent. As the barbarians approach from the west and the hooded warrior emerges from the south, Isabel grapples with the weight of her family''s secret and the thirst for survival. In a world where allies may lurk in the shadows and enemies wear the guise of daylight, Isabel must decide what risks she is willing to take and whom she is prepared to lose. Will this unexpected journey change the world, or will it be the world that changes Isabel?',1,'1752824337455.0','1752824337455.0','http://books.google.com/books/content?id=mfR40AEACAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api',NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO Books VALUES(49,'Ghost of a Threat','Beth Dolgner','Redglare Media','Fiction',NULL,'Redglare Media','2012-01-09','','English','New TBR','0984915613','Normal young women go on dates on Saturday nights. Paranormal investigator Betty "Boo" Boorman goes on ghost hunts in Savannah, Georgia, America''s most haunted city. She''s more comfortable around ghosts than guys, anyway. A violent haunting forces Betty to team up with her rival ghost hunter, the arrogant Carter Lansford. When the violence is turned toward her, though, Betty knows she needs additional expertise. She enlists the help of a handsome stranger, who introduces himself simply as Maxwell, Demon. Betty''s ghost hunting is cut short when she''s threatened and, finally, attacked. Either someone wants her to stay away from an investigation, or a demon hunter is targeting her. As Betty begins to fall for Maxwell''s mysterious charm, she starts to wonder if her life--and her soul--are worth the risk.',1,'1752824341370.0','1752824341370.0','http://books.google.com/books/content?id=3EWwtgAACAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api',NULL,NULL);
