INSERT INTO Books VALUES(121,'Ficciones','Jorge Luis Borges','Continental Book Company','Fiction','Fiction','Continental Book Company','1971','','Spanish','Spanish Fiction','UTEXAS:059173028018776','Resumen Se re├║nen en FICCIONES dos libros de Jorge Luis Borges fechados en 1941 y 1944. ┬½El jard├¡n de senderos que se bifurcan┬╗ incluye ocho relatos, entre los que cabe destacar dos breves narraciones de excepcional calidad: ┬½Pierre Menard, autor del Quijote┬╗ y ┬½La Biblioteca de Babel┬╗. ┬½Artificios┬╗ lo forman nueve cuentos, entre ellos ┬½La muerte y la br├║jula┬╗ (historia de una tortuosa venganza), ┬½Funes el memorioso┬╗ (una larga met├ífora del insomnio) y ┬½El Sur┬╗ (┬½acaso mi mejor cuento┬╗, en palabras del autor).',1,'1752826878116.0','1752826878116.0','http://books.google.com/books/content?id=DEpCAAAAYAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api',NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO Books VALUES(122,'Naked Lunch','William S. Burroughs','Grove Press','Fiction','Fiction','Grove Press','2013-07-16','','English','English Classics','0802122078','Since its original publication in Paris in 1959, Naked Lunch has become one of the most important novels of the twentieth century. Exerting its influence on the relationship of art and obscenity, it is one of the books that redefined not just literature but American culture. For the Burroughs enthusiast and the neophyte, this volumeΓÇöthat contains final-draft typescripts, numerous unpublished contemporaneous writings by Burroughs, his own later introductions to the book, and his essay on psychoactive drugsΓÇöis a valuable and fresh experience of a novel that has lost none of its relevance or satirical bite.',1,'1752826916123.0','1752826916123.0','http://books.google.com/books/content?id=5cUNmwEACAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api',NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO Books VALUES(123,'20,000 Leagues Under the Sea','Jules Verne','National Geographic Books','Fiction','Fiction','National Geographic Books','2010-10-05','','English','English Classics','9780451531698','Join Captain Nemo and the Nautilus as they journey into the deep in Jules VerneΓÇÖs classic science fiction tale. In an age that has seen the wildest speculations of science become reality, Jules Verne is regarded as both a technological prophet and one of the most exciting masters of imagination the world has ever known. Of all his novels, none is more compelling and thrilling than 20,000 Leagues Under the Sea. This extraordinary voyage into the depths of the unknown aboard the legendary submarine NautilusΓÇöcommanded by the brilliant, tragic Captain NemoΓÇöexplores both the limitless possibilities of science and the twisted labyrinth of the human mind. The novel stands as science fiction raised to the level of literature and remains a vivid expression of a new era of technological advancement and humanityΓÇÖs place within that world. Translated and with a Foreword by Mendor T. Brunetti Includes an Introduction by Stephen Baxter and an Afterword by Walter James Miller',1,'1752826918861.0','1752826918861.0','http://books.google.com/books/content?id=u8iNEAAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api',NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO Books VALUES(124,'From Hell. Nueva Edici├│n','Alan Moore, Eddie Campbell',NULL,'Fiction',NULL,NULL,'2013-04','','Spanish','Comics','8415480849','Reedici├│n de la obra completa de Moore y Campbell, revisada y complementada con comentarios de Alan Moore. Se trata de una revisitaci├│n del mito de Jack el Destripador, a su vez que una disecci├│n despiadada de la sociedad victoriana. Esta famosa novela gr├ífica ha sido galardonada con los prestigiosos premios Eisner y Harvey en diversas categor├¡as as├¡ como por el premio de la cr├¡tica del Festival de Angoulema 2001. Sin duda, una de las obras maestras del genio del c├│mic Alan Moore (Watchmen, La Liga de los Hombre Extraordinarios, V de Vendetta).',1,'1752826939917.0','1752826939917.0','http://books.google.com/books/content?id=VrV9mwEACAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api',NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO Books VALUES(125,'Bad Dreams in the Night','Adam Ellis',NULL,'Fiction','Comics & Graphic Novels',NULL,'2024-04-16','','English','Comics','1524887188','Like a graphic novel version of Scary Stories to Tell in the Dark, this collection of original horror tales is packed with urban legends, terrifying twists, and delightfully haunted stories by one of the biggest stars in webcomics. Each story will make you scream for more! A new take on a classic format, Bad Dreams in the Night is an updated, illustrated take on the horror anthologies the author grew up with as a kid, such as Scary Stories to Tell in the Dark and In a Dark, Dark Room. These self-contained stories grew rapidly in popularity among the author''s online audience, and even inspired production of a motion picture from Buzzfeed Studios and Lionsgate Films. Filled with spine-tingling, pulse-increasing tales of mystery and supernatural occurrences, this book of never-before-seen comics will be the perfect gift for people who love Black Mirror and Stranger Things and listened to podcasts like Welcome to Nightvale and Rabbits.',1,'1752826944336.0','1752826944336.0','http://books.google.com/books/content?id=d3kD0AEACAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api',NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO Books VALUES(126,'No. 5, Vol. 1','Taiyo Matsumoto','VIZ Media LLC','Fiction','Comics & Graphic Novels','VIZ Media LLC','2021-07-20','','English','Comics','1974720764','A powerfully imagined vision of the future from Taiyo Matsumoto, creator of the Eisner AwardΓÇôwinning Cats of the Louvre and Tekkonkinkreet. In a world where most of the earth has become a harsh desert, the Rainbow Council of the Peace Corps has a growing crisis on its hands. No. 5, one member of a team of superpowered global security guardians and a top marksman, has gone rogue. Now the other guardians have to hunt down No. 5 and his mysterious companion, Matryoshka. But why did No. 5 turn against the council, and what will it mean for the future of the world?',1,'1752826968627.0','1752826968627.0','http://books.google.com/books/content?id=_g8CzgEACAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api',NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO Books VALUES(127,'Saga Volume 1','Brian K Vaughan','Image Comics','Fiction','Comics & Graphic Novels','Image Comics','2012-10-23','','English','Comics','1607066017','Romeo & Juliet meets Star Wars in this sexy, subversive fantasy and sci-fi space opera about star-crossed lovers from enemy worlds. An epic for mature readers, SAGA is the story of Hazel, a child born to star-crossed parents from opposite sides of a never-ending galactic war. Now, Hazel''s fugitive family must risk everything to find a peaceful future in a harsh universe that values destruction over creation. The multiple award-winning, critically acclaimed masterpiece and one of the most iconic, bestselling comic book series of its time begins here in the first volume collecting issues #1-6. The SAGA series has sold over 7 million copies to date across all formats, has been translated into 20 languages, and has garnered multiple Eisner and Harvey Awards, plus a Hugo Award, British Fantasy Award, Goodreads Choice Award, Shuster Award, Inkwell Award, Ringo Award, and more. It has been featured in such mainstream media outlets as TIME, Entertainment Weekly, The Atlantic, NPR, and beyond, and has become a pop culture phenomenon. Select praise for SAGA: ΓÇ£The kind of comic that you get when truly talented superstar creators are given the freedom to produce their dream comic.ΓÇ¥ ΓÇöEntertainment Weekly ΓÇ£An unwieldy, profane, and glorious ode to compassion and equality.ΓÇ¥ ΓÇöThe Atlantic "A little bit Romeo & Juliet and a lot Star Wars." ΓÇöUSA Today "Mischievous, vulgar and gloriously inventive." ΓÇöTIME Magazine "May it run for 1,000 issues." ΓÇöRolling Stone Magazine',1,'1752826993065.0','1752826993065.0',NULL,NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO Books VALUES(128,'Eclipse Volume 1','Zachary Kaplan','Image Comics','Fiction','Comics & Graphic Novels','Image Comics','2017-02-21','','English','Comics','1534300384','Imagine if sunlight burned you alive. In the near future, a mysterious solar event has transformed the sunΓÇÖs light into deadly immolating rays. The worldΓÇÖs few survivors now live in nocturnal cities. But a killer emerges who uses sunlight to burn his victims, and when he targets the daughter of a solar power mogul, it falls to a disillusioned solar engineer to protect her. Collects issues 1 through 4.',1,'1752827032518.0','1752827032518.0','http://books.google.com/books/content?id=3UE5vgAACAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api',NULL,NULL);
